        <h1>
            Review of Mattermost Interoperability Characteristics
        </h1>
<p><strong>GET/POST APIs with Mattermost</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Mattermost provides a number of GET/POST APIs which can we used by clients and third party applications to interact with the server.
These APIs are collectively called as Mattermost Web Services API.
</li>
<li>
Mattermost also allows developers to create bots.
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>1. How can we achieve calling (custom GET/POST)APIs?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
    we can call any of the APIs by hitting the endpoint and passing the required parameters along with credentials for authentication.
</li>
<li>There are a number of endpoints provided by Mattermost to achieve different functionalities. 
    a detailed description of all the available endpoints can be found here: <a href=https://api.mattermost.com/#tag/introduction>https://api.mattermost.com/#tag/introduction</a>
</li>
<li> Introduction to creating some sample bots can be found <a href=https://docs.mattermost.com/deployment/bots.html>here</a>.
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>2. What resources are required for producing or providing it?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>We should have correct level of access on the platform to be able to call the APIs.</li>
<li>The REST APIs provided by Mattermost are available out of the box.</li>
<li>A detailed description of all the available endpoints can be found here: <a href=https://api.mattermost.com/#tag/introduction>https://api.mattermost.com/#tag/introduction</a>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>3. Are there any standards surrounding the product that we have to follow?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li> we must adhere to security and regulation guidelines.<a href=https://docs.mattermost.com/guides/administrator.html#mattermost-compliance>here</a>.</li>
</ul>
